correctness.rationale: Several key fields are correct (PEALD method; DADI/TEGa/DEZ with O2 plasma at 600 W; pressure 0.76 Torr; 200 °C; substrate; film thickness 35 nm; BGTC device; amorphous by XRD; mobility ≈47.4 cm2/Vs; Vth ≈ −2.88 V). However, many entries are ungrounded, incorrect, or unit-inconsistent, and multiple processes described in the article are not represented. Major issues: (1) Missing processes: The article reports at least two ALD supercycle designs (A and A′) and also discusses B/B′ (and C); only one process is extracted. (2) Supercycle misrepresentation: For A, In sub-cycles are 14 → Ga 3 → In 14 → Zn 4 (total In = 28). The extraction lists only one InOx count of 14 and sets an “atomicRatio” of 14:3:4, which is not a measured atomic ratio and does not match the actual supercycle totals; also it is labeled as XPS depth profile but no such ratio is reported. (3) Hallucinated process parameters not in the paper: growth-per-cycle values, dosing times, purge times, flow rates, saturation flag, nucleation period, delivery method, carrier/purging gas (Ar), reactor manufacturer, optical properties (n, absorption, band gap), uniformity, conformality, roughness, on/off ratio, and otherAspects (filmStability/reproducibility). These are not traceable to the text. (4) Unit/value errors: resistivity taken from 1.85×10^-2 Ω·cm was entered as 0.0185 Ω·m (off by 100×); carrier density reported as 7.90×10^19 cm^-3 was entered with unit C·m^-3 and without cm^-3→m^-3 conversion (should be 7.90×10^25 m^-3 if using PER-M3, or multiply by q for C·m^-3); subthreshold swing 0.22 V/dec was encoded as 0.22 mV (should be 220 mV if using MilliV); film density 6.51 g·cm^-3 was given with unit g·dm^-3 but numeric value 6.51 (should be 6510 g·dm^-3 if that unit is used). (5) numberofCycles=35 is unjustified (confuses film thickness with cycle count; the article does not state number of ALD cycles). (6) Film composition: “elementalConcentration” 68% is ambiguous and not mapped to a specific element; the cited method (“XPS depth profile analysis”) is inaccurate (AES was used for depth profiling; XPS provided surface composition). Corrections needed: add separate processes for A and A′ (and B/B′ if extracted), fix supercycle counts (In should appear twice with 14 each or a total of 28), remove or leave unspecified any parameters not reported, correct all unit conversions (resistivity, carrier density, SS, film density), remove unsubstantiated optical/uniformity/conformality/roughness/on–off values, correct reactor details and carrier/purge gases only if stated, and ensure film composition fields reflect the actual reported measurements with proper methods and traceability.

completeness.rationale: Major omissions and many untraceable/incorrect values. (1) Multiple processes are described in the article (at minimum A and A′; additionally B, C, and B′), but only one process is extracted. Supercycle A′ (Zn→In→Ga→In) and others are missing; thus the extraction does not capture all experiments. (2) Several parameters are invented and not supported by the text: growth-per-cycle for InOx/GaOx/ZnO, total number of cycles (35), dosing/purge times, flow rates, saturation, nucleation period, delivery method, uniformity (5%), conformality (AR=10), roughness (1.2 nm), band gap (3.2 eV), on/off ratio (1e6), safety, and reproducibility. These lack traceability. (3) Supercycle design is incompletely represented: numberofSubcycles lists InOx=14 once but the sequence contains InOx twice (split 14+14); A′ sequence is omitted. (4) Film composition is misrepresented: atomicRatio '14:3:4' is a design ratio, not a measured elemental ratio; labeling it as XPS-derived is incorrect. ElementalConcentration=68% is ambiguous (no element specified) and mismatched to the article’s XPS/XRF data. (5) Unit/quantity errors: Hall resistivity is reported in the article as 1.85×10^-2 Ω·cm but extracted as 0.0185 Ω·m (100× too large); carrier density 7.9×10^19 cm^-3 is copied without conversion to m^-3 (should be ~7.9×10^25 m^-3) and the unit uses C-PER-M3 instead of PER-M3; subthreshold swing is 0.22 V/dec in the article but extracted with a MilliV unit. (6) Some fields are speculative (e.g., carrier/purge gas = Ar; reactor manufacturer = AP systems) and not stated in the paper. Required additions/revisions: add separate process entries for A and A′ (and B, C, B′ if in scope), correct supercycle sequences and counts (including split In sub-cycles), remove or leave unspecified any parameters not reported, fix resistivity and carrier density unit conversions, correct SS units, and revise film composition data to match reported XPS/XRF values.
